Potbelly is great. Food is great for what it is. Prices are reasonable. The coffee is pretty good too if you come for breakfast. The staff is really friendly and goes out of their way to ask about your day, give you a free birthday sandwich, etc. If you haven't been to potbelly before, make sure you get the hot peppers on whatever sandwich you get. They're the best part.

It's the exact same as any other Potbelly in terms of food, but it took so long to get my sandwich I almost missed my bus!

I normally go there for the strawberry shakes. They have an X-Large size which many other places do not. This is good for those hot summer days when you just crave something cold and lots of it. The shakes have lots of real fruit chunks in it which adds to the treat.  The atmosphere in every Potbelly spot i've been in is good to sit down in. The staff is always happy and courteous. Try this place out.
